<h4 id="section-animationstyle">animationStyle <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  The name of the animation style to use for open and close animations. See {{link-to "animations" "documentation.animations"}} for more details.
</p>


<h4 id="section-listwidth">listWidth <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  Width of the popup. You must pass in a CSS size value with the unit. The select uses CSS box-sizing to ensure precentage-based sizes are actual sizes. A width smaller than the width of the select will be ignored.
</p>


<h4 id="section-size">size <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  The overall size of the select. Width is set via the <a href="#section-width">width</a> parameter. Each size has an associated width it will use unless you override it.
</p>

<h5>Values</h5>
<ul class="defaults">
  <li>tiny</li>
  <li>small</li>
  <li>medium (default)</li>
  <li>large</li>
</ul>
<p>
  Additional sizes can be added via CSS. See {{link-to "Theming" "documentation.theming"}}
</p>

<pre>\{{eui-select placeholder="Select a country" options=countries size='tiny'}}
\{{eui-select placeholder="Select a country" options=countries size='small'}}
\{{eui-select placeholder="Select a country" options=countries size='medium'}}
\{{eui-select placeholder="Select a country" options=countries size='large'}}</pre>

<div class="output">
  {{eui-select placeholder="Select a country" options=countries size='tiny'}}
  {{eui-select placeholder="Select a country" options=countries size='small'}}
  {{eui-select placeholder="Select a country" options=countries size='medium'}}
  {{eui-select placeholder="Select a country" options=countries size='large'}}
</div>


<h4 id="section-style">style <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  Aesthetic style of the select. The styles are shared with the <em>button</em> component.
</p>

<h5>Values</h5>
<ul class="defaults">
  <li>default (default)</li>
  <li>primary</li>
</ul>

<div class="output">
  {{eui-select placeholder="Select a country" options=countries style='default'}}
  {{eui-select placeholder="Select a country" options=countries style='primary'}}
</div>



<h4 id="section-width">width <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  Width of the select. You must pass in a CSS size value with the unit. The select uses CSS box-sizing to ensure precentage-based sizes are actual sizes.
</p>

<pre>\{{eui-input width='150px' placeholder='150px'}}
\{{eui-input width='15em' placeholder='15em'}}
\{{eui-input width='30%' placeholder='30%'}}</pre>

<div class="output">
  {{eui-select options=countries width='150px' placeholder='150px'}}
  {{eui-select options=countries width='15em' placeholder='15em'}}
  {{eui-select options=countries width='30%' placeholder='30%'}}
</div>


<h4 id="section-disabled">disabled <span>boolean</span></h4>
<p>
  Disables the select.
</p>

<pre>\{{eui-select options=countries placeholder='Country' disabled=true}}
\{{eui-select options=countries disabled=true value=1}}</pre>

<div class="output">
  {{eui-select options=countries placeholder='Select a Country' disabled=true}}
  {{eui-select options=countries disabled=true value=1}}
</div>


<h4 id="section-labelpath">labelPath <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  Path to the label property for each of the <em>options</em>. Default path is 'label'.
</p>


<h4 id="section-options">options <span>array</span></h4>
<p>
  An array of options for the user to select from.
</p>

<pre>countries: [
  { label: 'Canada', value: 1 }
  { label: 'United Sates', value: 2 }
  { label: 'Mexico', value: 3 }
]</pre>

<pre>users: [
  Ember.Object.create({
    name: 'John',
    email: 'john@gmail.com',
    value: '1'
  }), Ember.Object.create({
    name: 'Mark',
    email: 'mark@gmail.com',
    value: '2'
  }), Ember.Object.create({
    name: 'Richard',
    email: 'richard@gmail.com',
    value: '3'
  })
]</pre>

<p>
  You will also need to specify the path to the label property using <em>labelPath</em>.
</p>

<pre>\{{eui-select placeholder="Select by name" options=users labelPath='name'}}
\{{eui-select placeholder="Select by email" options=users labelPath='email'}}</pre>

<div class="output">
  {{eui-select placeholder="Select by name" options=users labelPath='name'}}
  {{eui-select placeholder="Select by email" options=users labelPath='email'}}
</div>


<h4 id="section-placeholder">placeholder <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  Placeholder value for the select.
</p>

<pre>\{{eui-select placeholder='Select a Country' options=countries}}</pre>

<div class="output">
  {{eui-select placeholder='Select a Country' options=countries}}
</div>


<h4 id="section-required">required <span>boolean</span></h4>
<p>
  If set to true no blank option will be inserted into the option list. Defaults to <em>false</em>
</p>


<h4 id="section-selection">selection <span>object</span></h4>
<p>
  The currently selected option. <em>null</em> if nothing is selected.
</p>


<h4 id="section-value">value <span>object</span></h4>
<p>
  Uses the <em>valuePath</em> property to look up the value of the current <em>selection</em>.
</p>
<p>
  If you do not specify a <em>selection</em> for the select, then the <em>value</em> and <em>valuePath</em> properties will be used to find the option that corresponds with the value in the list of <em>options</em>. The corresponding option will then be assigned to the <em>selection</em> as its initial value.
</p>


<h4 id="section-valuepath">valuePath <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  Path to the value property for each of the <em>options</em>. Default path is 'value'.
</p>


<h4 id="section-error">error <span>boolean | string</span></h4>
<p>
  Responsible for validation and error handling. See {{link-to "Error Handling" "documentation.errorhandling"}}
</p>


<h4 id="section-forceerrorcheck">forceErrorCheck <span>boolean</span></h4>
<p>
  If set to <em>true</em> the select will force an error check, even if the value is blank.
</p>
